cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.OS, cs.DS

This paper deals with network measurements and classification of ICMP timestamp responses, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the leaking of information about the host, which could be related to operating systems (cs.OS) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the methodology used for classification could be considered as a form of machine learning or data mining (cs.SI).
